    Previously, he co-founded a company called <b>Nation</b>. Backed by Placeholder, M13, Slow, Circle, and Tribe Ventures, the company went on to build a handful of software products, in the end resulting in Vellum before the team disbanded. Before Nation, he was a Senior Designer at Waybridge (acq. Minehub).<br /><br />
    He began his career as the youngest designer ever hired at the prolific brand transformation agency, <a href="https://wearecollins.com/">COLLINS</a>. He is the author of a 2018 book, <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Dropout-Manifesto-educational-institution-schooling/dp/1980887683">The Dropout Manifesto</a>.
    <br /><br />
    <span class="text-neutral-800 font-bold">He is <a href="https://instagram.com/messybirkin">@messybirkin</a> on <a href="https://instagram.com/messybirkin">Instagram</a> and <a href="https://x.com/messybirkin">X</a>, and is reachable via <a href="mailto:diegosegura@hey.com">email</a>.</span>
